{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum Hamming weight of the product of 2023 and n. Since n can be any positive integer, this is equivalent to finding the minimum number of ones in the binary representation of any multiple of 2023. This is a problem of finding the smallest weight of a multiple of a given integer.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine the prime factorization of 2023. Specifically, check if 2023 is divisible by 7, 11, 13, 17, or other small primes to understand its structure in binary."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Investigate the properties of the Hamming weight of multiples of an odd integer m. Specifically, for m = 2023, determine if there exists an n such that 2023*n is a power of 2 (which would give k(n)=1) or a sum of two powers of 2 (which would give k(n)=2). If not, check for k(n)=3, and so on."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_3",
      "instructions": "Test the condition for k(n) = 1. This requires 2023 to be a power of 2, which is false. Test the condition for k(n) = 2. This requires 2023 to divide 2^a + 2^b for some integers a and b. This is equivalent to checking if 2^a + 2^b is congruent to 0 modulo 2023, or 2^(a-b) is congruent to -1 modulo 2023 (assuming a > b). Use modular arithmetic to check if -1 is in the cyclic subgroup generated by 2 modulo 2023."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_4",
      "instructions": "If k(n) = 2 is impossible, test if k(n) = 3 is possible. This requires 2023 to divide 2^a + 2^b + 2^c. This is equivalent to checking if there exist integers such that 2^x + 2^y + 1 is congruent to 0 modulo 2023 (after dividing by the smallest power of 2)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "1. Use helper_1 to confirm the prime factors of 2023. 2. Use helper_3 to check if k(n)=1 or k(n)=2 is possible by examining the order of 2 modulo 2023 and whether -1 is a power of 2 modulo 2023. 3. If k(n)=2 is impossible, use helper_4 to check if k(n)=3 is possible by testing if 2^x + 2^y + 1 is divisible by 2023 for small x, y. 4. The smallest k(n) found through this incremental search is the final answer."
}

